documentation.text:
@dev Safely transfers `tokenId` token from `from` to `to`, checking first that contract recipients
 are aware of the ERC721 protocol to prevent tokens from being forever locked.
 `_data` is additional data, it has no specified format and it is sent in call to `to`.
 This internal function is equivalent to {safeTransferFrom}, and can be used to e.g.
 implement alternative mechanisms to perform token transfer, such as signature-based.
 Requirements:
 - `from` cannot be the zero address.
 - `to` cannot be the zero address.
 - `tokenId` token must exist and be owned by `from`.
 - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC721Receiver-onERC721Received}, which is called upon a safe transfer.
 Emits a {Transfer} event.

baseURI().details: Returns the base URI set via {_setBaseURI}. This will be automatically added as a prefix in {tokenURI} to each token's URI, or to the token ID if no specific URI is set for that token ID.

callback(uint256,string).details: Updates a certain token URI and clears the corresponding update request Only the assigned server oracle is allowed to call this function

changeNameAndOrPosition(uint256,string,s.details: Changes the name and/or position of a given NFT, must be owned by the caller. Whenever such change is made, it is first immediately reflected in the Card struct, and in the metadata after oracle updates. User can change both name and position, just the name, or just the position (by leaving those inputs empty)

constructor.details: Initializes the contract by setting a `name` and a `symbol` to the token collection, and defining base and default URIs.

defaultURI().details: Returns the default URI set via {_setBaseURI}. This will be automatically added as a prefix in {tokenURI} to each token's URI, or to the token ID if no specific URI is set for that token ID.

getCard(string,string).details: Mints a new NFT Business Card

isNameReserved(string).details: Returns if the name has been reserved. Name reservation checks are made in lowercase

modifyUpdatePrice(uint256).details: Changes the update price for the usage of the oracle

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setBaseURI(string).details: For setting the baseURI for all tokenId's.

setDefaultURI(string).details: For setting the default URI for all tokenId's.

setOracle(address).details: Sets up a new oracle that handles the dynamic aspect of the NFT

startSale().details: Starts the sale, cannot do so until the oracle is defined

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: See {IERC165-supportsInterface}. Time complexity O(1), guaranteed to always use less than 30 000 gas.

swapNameAndPosition(uint256,uint256).details: Swaps the name and position between two NFTs, must be owned by the caller. This is to give customers the ability to directly shuffle name and positions of their cards, and prevent possible "name snipers"

tokenStats(uint256).details: Returns the stats of a token

tokenURI(uint256).details: Overrides the default tokenURI behaviour to include the default URI

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateTokenURI(uint256).details: Updates the tokenURI, intented to be used only when oracle fails to update a tokenURI

withdraw().details: Withdraw balance from this contract (Callable by owner)
